Preconditions:
The input parameter `n` must be a positive integer.
The input parameter `edges` must be a non-null 2D array.
The number of rows in the `edges` array must be equal to `n-1`.
Each row in the `edges` array must contain exactly 2 elements.
The elements in each row of the `edges` array must be integers.
The elements in each row of the `edges` array must be within the range of 1 to `n`.
The elements in each row of the `edges` array must be distinct.

Postconditions:
The returned array must be of size `n-1`.
Each element in the returned array must be an integer.
The returned array must be in 1-indexed order.
The maximum distance between any two cities in each subtree must be equal to the index of the corresponding element in the returned array.
The sum of all elements in the returned array must be equal to the total number of subtrees.